results.name: a(n) = 1 + Sum_{ k < n and k | n} a(k).
comment: Permanent of n X n (0,1) matrix defined by A(i,j)=1 iff j=1 or i divides j. - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Jul 05 2003
Partial sums of A074206, ordered factorizations. - _Augustine O. Munagi_, Jul 10 2007
link: Herbert S. Wilf, The Redheffer matrix of a partially ordered set, The Electronic Journal of Combinatorics, Volume 11(2), 2004, R#10.
formula: a(n) = 1 + Sum_{k = 2 to n} a([n/k]) [From Mitchell Lee (worthawholephan(AT)gmail.com), Jul 26 2010]
xref: A173382 is an essentially identical sequence.
